seal     : Money is the strangest technology humans ever built: a shared fiction so useful it became real. It is not the gold or the paper — it is the agreement, the ledger everyone trusts. Money is the memory of who owes whom, made portable; a measure of value, a means of exchange, and a store of trust. When the trust breaks, the money is just paper again.
